content: As an AI language model, I do not have personal preferences, but Conwy Castle is one of the most popular and impressive tourist attractions in North Wales. It has a rich history and is surrounded by stunning scenery, including the Conwy River and Snowdonia National Park. The castle is also well-preserved, so you can explore the towers, walkways, and dungeons while getting a sense of what it was like to live in a fortress during the Middle Ages.
